history.text: Hello, this is the fire department dispatcher. We're monitoring a wildfire close to your location and need to ensure your safety. Are you currently safe at home?
The fire is advancing at 3 mph, and wind gusts are expected to reach 25 mph. You must evacuate immediately via Route 45 north.
The fire is now within 2 miles of your area. Please leave your home within the next 15 minutes to avoid being trapped.
The fire has intensified, and smoke is reducing visibility. Evacuate now, taking Route 45 north, and avoid any side roads.
The evacuation order remains in effect. Ensure you have essential items and leave immediately; conditions are deteriorating rapidly.
Please stay safe and evacuate now. Goodbye.

scenario: You are at home when you notice smoke in the distance. A wildfire is spreading rapidly. Your phone rings—it's the fire department.
